<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1305,1509]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,304,1305,1330]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe north to south 
<collectingCountry box="[581,666,1305,1329]" name="Finland" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Finland</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[729,820,1305,1329]" name="Sweden" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Sweden</collectingCountry>
, Asia, North Africa to 
<collectingCountry box="[1096,1166,1306,1330]" name="Egypt" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Egypt</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1181,1243,1305,1329]" name="Israel" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Israel</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Westrich" box="[1261,1432,1305,1329]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Westrich, P. (1989) Die Wildbienen Baden-Wurttembergs. Band. 1 und 2. Eugen Ulmer Verlag, Stuttgart, 972 pp." type="book" year="1989">
Westrich 
<number box="[1373,1432,1305,1329]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1989.0">1989</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Warncke" box="[151,317,1341,1365]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Warncke, K. (1992) Die Westpalaarktischen Arten der Bienengattung Sphecodes Latr. (Hymenoptera, Apidae, Halictinae). Bericht der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft Augsburg, 52, 9 - 64." type="journal article" year="1992">
Warncke 
<number box="[257,317,1341,1365]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[336,385,1342,1365]" name="Iran" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1305,1509]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,297,1377,1402]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Biology.</emphasis>
Species of warm sandy biotopes, in south Europe quite common, in central Europe local but in sandy localities usually abundant. The only confirmed host is 
<taxonomicName box="[773,1051,1413,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villosulum">
<emphasis box="[773,1051,1413,1437]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Lasioglossum villosulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Alfken" box="[1215,1379,1413,1437]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Alfken, J. D. (1913) Die Bienenfauna von Bremen. Abhandlungen des naturwissenschaflichen Vereins Bremen, 22, 1 - 220. Alfken, J. D. (1914) Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Bienenfauna von Algerien. Memoires de la Societe Entomologique Belgique, 22, 185 - 237." type="journal article" year="1913">
Alfken (
<number box="[1309,1370,1413,1437]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1913.0">1913</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bischoff" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Bischoff, H. (1927) Biologie der Hymenopteren. J. Springer, Berlin, 598 pp." type="book" year="1927">
Bischoff (
<number box="[226,284,1449,1473]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1927.0">1927</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
put 
<taxonomicName authority="Schenck" authorityName="Schenck" box="[347,621,1449,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicorne">
<emphasis box="[347,498,1449,1473]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">L. brevicorne</emphasis>
(Schenck)
</taxonomicName>
as likely host. We confirm both hosts and have observed 
<taxonomicName box="[1286,1436,1450,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puncticeps">
<emphasis box="[1286,1436,1450,1473]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">S. puncticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also in an association with 
<taxonomicName box="[453,568,1485,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="politum">
<emphasis box="[453,568,1485,1509]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">L. politum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Warncke" authorityName="Warncke" box="[623,900,1485,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabulosum">
<emphasis box="[623,772,1485,1509]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">L. sabulosum</emphasis>
(Warncke)
</taxonomicName>
, but with no evidence.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
